00:18:54.800 --> 00:18:59.840
[Guest]: to force me to go down and play a sport. But she's like, oh, sport leads to teamwork, it leads to

00:18:59.840 --> 00:19:05.920
[Guest]: building character and blah, blah, blah. And I'm like, no, I'm just bored. It tires me and I don't

00:19:05.920 --> 00:19:10.880
[Guest]: want to do this. I just want to be this lazy boy and sit at home and read. Which sounds like an

00:19:10.880 --> 00:19:15.200
[Amit Varma]: excuse not of a gay man, but also a Bengali man. I mean, half Bengali. I mean, who wants to

00:19:15.200 --> 00:19:23.040
[Guest]: do physical activity and sweat? I'm sorry, I don't want to perspire. I just don't I'm, I'm, I'm not,

00:19:23.040 --> 00:19:28.480
[Guest]: I'm just averse to the idea of my pores, emitting something that I don't want on my on my skin.

00:19:28.480 --> 00:19:32.800
[Amit Varma]: That's all. And you mentioned voodoo. And there's a nice quote about voodoo in your book, which I'll

00:19:32.800 --> 00:19:37.840
[Amit Varma]: again read out, quote, voodoo makes you not want to look in the mirror. Once you get out from there,

00:19:37.840 --> 00:19:42.720
[Amit Varma]: there is this heavy sadness in the air, in the low ceiling, the expression that is still muted.

00:19:42.720 --> 00:19:47.040
[Amit Varma]: And with all the strangers, it doesn't make it much easier. Stop good and voodoo, of course,

00:19:47.040 --> 00:19:52.480
[Amit Varma]: is this gay club that you went to to meet people and yet there was no option you all of you had to

00:19:52.480 --> 00:19:59.360
[Guest]: be there because how else do you? Yeah, initially, till gay Bombay party started. And then you went

00:19:59.360 --> 00:20:03.520
[Guest]: on and even there, there was such a class difference. Like there was something called

00:20:03.520 --> 00:20:08.560
[Guest]: Salvation Star, which was just for the South Bombayites. Oh, and if you were say from

00:20:09.760 --> 00:20:12.320
[Guest]: out of South Bombay, and you would come to that party,

00:20:14.080 --> 00:20:18.000
[Guest]: somehow they would sense you, I think they would smell you that you're not from South Bombay.

00:20:18.000 --> 00:20:20.640
[Guest]: The other. Yeah, the other and they would treat you like that.

00:20:21.360 --> 00:20:25.440
[Guest]: Well, and you would be shunned into a corner and nobody would show any interest in you.

00:20:25.440 --> 00:20:31.440
[Guest]: And then there was a gay Bombay party culture at Velocity in Tarde, where every Saturday,

00:20:31.440 --> 00:20:35.600
[Guest]: there used to be a party. And just the idea of going there with your other friends,

00:20:36.240 --> 00:20:42.880
[Guest]: or with your friends and just dancing to item songs and, and just living, getting drunk and

00:20:42.880 --> 00:20:48.160
[Guest]: to be able to grind against each other, a stranger even and make out on the dance floor.

00:20:48.160 --> 00:20:53.840
[Guest]: It just gives you such a sense of liberation. And this is all pre 377. Yeah, we just absolutely

00:20:53.840 --> 00:20:58.960
[Guest]: snatched what we got. At least I did that. I remember my moments of just snatching,

00:20:58.960 --> 00:21:04.400
[Guest]: of just grabbing with both hands and not being apologetic about it at all. And I guess privilege

00:21:04.400 --> 00:21:09.360
[Guest]: had a very big role to play. Because in my head, I knew that I was cushioned and comfort

00:21:09.360 --> 00:21:17.200
[Guest]: was there to whatever extent back home. So I could manage to put myself out here and do this.

00:21:17.840 --> 00:21:21.440
[Amit Varma]: But it must have been much harder, for example, from the non South Bombay types who happened to

00:21:21.440 --> 00:21:27.120
[Amit Varma]: come to the Salvation Star party. And what do you do? I mean, it's, I think you, you have added

00:21:27.120 --> 00:21:34.080
[Guest]: insecurities, you learn, you find your own tribe. Because it's so important to find your tribe

00:21:34.080 --> 00:21:39.360
[Guest]: when you're like, for me, while growing up in college, I was dying to speak with another gay

00:21:39.360 --> 00:21:45.280
[Guest]: boy. And I literally thought to take a quote from Little Britain, that I was the only gay man in the

00:21:45.280 --> 00:21:51.200
[Guest]: village. There was nobody else. And it frustrated me no end till of course, internet came about.

00:21:51.200 --> 00:21:56.560
[Guest]: And I was like, Oh, there are other people. And there are other people very close by.

00:21:57.840 --> 00:22:02.160
[Amit Varma]: And I guess the internet came at just the right time. And how has the internet changed things?

00:22:02.160 --> 00:22:05.360
[Amit Varma]: Like are there still gay Bombay meetups? Is that still a necessity?

00:22:05.360 --> 00:22:10.400
[Guest]: Gay Bombay parties? Yeah, sure. Sure, sure. Those still go on. But now I've stopped going.

00:22:10.400 --> 00:22:14.560
[Amit Varma]: And you mentioned that there are more hookup apps for gay men than for straight men.

00:22:14.560 --> 00:22:18.480
[Guest]: Gay men are everywhere. Gay people are everywhere. We are on Tinder, we are on Grindr,

00:22:18.480 --> 00:22:25.040
[Guest]: which is exclusively for us. We are on something called Planet Romeo. We are on Bumble. We are on

00:22:26.240 --> 00:22:34.960
[Guest]: Hinge. Yeah, everywhere. And I think also with 377 gone, a lot of men are coming out.

00:22:35.680 --> 00:22:41.040
[Guest]: They are coming out as bi curious. I don't know what that means. Or as curious or as bisexual or

00:22:41.040 --> 00:22:46.320
[Guest]: whatever label they want to give themselves. But they also making themselves seen that you know,

00:22:46.320 --> 00:22:51.280
[Guest]: this is us. And you know, we are out here. Actually, people have it on their Twitter profile,

00:22:51.280 --> 00:22:58.160
[Guest]: that they're bi curious, bi poly, bi curious, bisexual, trying to figure trying to navigate

00:22:58.160 --> 00:23:04.880
[Guest]: waters. Again, I don't know what that means. But, but yeah, I think it's a very good thing that

00:23:05.440 --> 00:23:09.280
[Amit Varma]: all of this is happening. It's a great thing that a lot of people who had these sort of

00:23:09.280 --> 00:23:15.040
[Amit Varma]: repressed feelings can now just come out in the open. And like a friend of mine was recently

00:23:15.040 --> 00:23:18.400
[Amit Varma]: telling me and he's otherwise I've known him as heterosexual. He has a girlfriend and all that.

00:23:18.400 --> 00:23:23.280
[Amit Varma]: But he said that he wanted to go to Grindr and check it out and see what the curiosity, right?

00:23:23.280 --> 00:23:30.400
