00:24:56.080 --> 00:25:01.520
[Guest]: even plan it that it would go this way. I thought he would slap me. I thought I'm done for. He was

00:25:01.520 --> 00:25:07.520
[Guest]: this huge Delhi boy. And I was like, Oh, my God. And that time I was scared of Delhi boys. I mean,

00:25:07.520 --> 00:25:13.280
[Guest]: I was like, okay, you know, and I'm trying to take him home. That was another kettle of fish

00:25:13.280 --> 00:25:20.400
[Guest]: all together. So I think we just, I was just a little brave and stupid. Because it could have

00:25:20.400 --> 00:25:26.480
[Guest]: gone anywhere. I could have just not been here. I could have been murdered in the taxi or something.

00:25:26.480 --> 00:25:32.000
[Guest]: And I say it with all earnestness, because these things used to happen. People wouldn't know about

00:25:32.000 --> 00:25:38.880
[Guest]: it. I think a lot of gay hate crime was very prevalent. I don't know if it still is.

00:25:38.880 --> 00:25:40.160
[Guest]: Have you experienced any of that?

00:25:40.720 --> 00:25:47.440
[Guest]: I've experienced verbal hate. A lot of it. I mean, in school, college, bullying.

00:25:48.000 --> 00:25:52.240
[Amit Varma]: In fact, one of the painful parts of your book is where you know, for a few pages, you describe

00:25:52.240 --> 00:25:56.880
