00:26:03.840 --> 00:26:09.440
[Guest]: the fact that I still remember it the way I do after all these years, should say something but,

00:26:09.440 --> 00:26:16.800
[Guest]: but yeah, but these things happened. And I don't know if they happened to every gay boy growing up.

00:26:17.440 --> 00:26:19.840
[Guest]: But universally, yes, these things happen.

00:26:19.840 --> 00:26:25.280
[Amit Varma]: And, and, you know, so let's, let's take this opportunity to sort of go back to your school

00:26:25.280 --> 00:26:29.920
[Amit Varma]: days where you talk about how okay, you had a sheltered life at home and everything is fine.

00:26:29.920 --> 00:26:33.440
[Amit Varma]: But then you go to school and everything changes. And again, quote from your book,

00:26:34.160 --> 00:26:39.200
[Amit Varma]: quote, consider this, a boy who has never been short on confidence, suddenly finds himself at

00:26:39.200 --> 00:26:43.360
[Amit Varma]: a loss for words when it comes to defending himself at school. He just cannot speak.

00:26:43.360 --> 00:26:48.080
[Amit Varma]: He has no idea what has beset his life. And before he can call out for his dad or mom,

00:26:48.080 --> 00:26:52.880
[Amit Varma]: he is surrounded by bullies, bullies who do not lose a single opportunity to make his life

00:26:52.880 --> 00:26:56.640
[Amit Varma]: miserable, stop quote. And to some extent that this is because the sense that

00:26:56.640 --> 00:27:01.680
[Guest]: Yeah, yeah, I think I think children, like we all know, can be very crude. And they have,

00:27:02.240 --> 00:27:08.560
[Guest]: they have the sense that perhaps adults just do not, this instinct that something is off in a way

00:27:08.560 --> 00:27:13.920
[Guest]: that this person is different. Like, I think it just started from the time I refused to

00:27:13.920 --> 00:27:20.960
[Guest]: be in any sports club or engage beyond like, I wouldn't want to wrestle in the mud.

00:27:22.080 --> 00:27:29.360
[Guest]: I wouldn't want to pick a fight just for no reason. So the angst or teenage angst just got

00:27:29.360 --> 00:27:36.320
[Guest]: channelized in other ways. So I think they picked on that a very, very, they didn't know.

00:27:37.360 --> 00:27:42.720
[Guest]: And children know. And they know how to pick on weaknesses, just like Lord of the Flies.

00:27:42.720 --> 00:27:45.440
[Amit Varma]: Yeah, which is very accurate.

00:27:46.000 --> 00:27:51.840
[Guest]: Yeah. And they just, so I felt like piggy. Just that, I think I came out of it

00:27:51.840 --> 00:27:53.520
[Guest]: a sane at the end of it all.

00:27:53.520 --> 00:27:55.200
[Guest]: How did you navigate your school years?

00:27:56.000 --> 00:28:01.600
[Guest]: I hid. And I did a very good job of hiding. So the dichotomy there, right? I mean, in school,

00:28:01.600 --> 00:28:05.840
[Guest]: you want to be hidden. But the minute you're out of school, and you're exploring your sexuality,

00:28:05.840 --> 00:28:11.760
[Guest]: you just want to be seen. So, and seen in a way that, that again, you don't want to be seen

00:28:11.760 --> 00:28:14.640
[Guest]: out there. But in a very subtle manner that

00:28:14.640 --> 00:28:17.040
[Amit Varma]: you want people who are looking for it to know that

00:28:17.040 --> 00:28:20.000
[Guest]: Yeah, that you're giving it. Yeah, that you're available.

00:28:20.000 --> 00:28:22.080
[Unknown]: Did you know any other gay boys in school?

00:28:22.720 --> 00:28:23.200
[Amit Varma]: No.

00:28:23.200 --> 00:28:26.400
[Amit Varma]: Which is weird, because just going by the percentages, there must have been a few.

00:28:26.400 --> 00:28:30.720
[Guest]: Of course, a more than few. I don't want to name my school, but notorious.

00:28:32.560 --> 00:28:36.320
[Guest]: Notorious in the sense that people say, Oh, a lot of homosexuals in your school.

00:28:36.320 --> 00:28:42.560
[Guest]: Oh, really? I didn't know anyone. I wish I did. But sometimes even the bullies, right?

00:28:42.560 --> 00:28:48.960
[Guest]: Could be. And they may not even have known that about themselves, unfortunately.

00:28:48.960 --> 00:28:52.000
[Guest]: Or some hidden kind of self loathing, which is expressing itself.

00:28:52.000 --> 00:28:58.160
[Guest]: And yeah, so a lot of psychological drama. So yeah, thank God it wasn't a boarding school.

00:28:58.960 --> 00:29:00.720
